==English==

===Etymology===
Old French, from an unattested Old Norse word which was probably the source also of [[wile]].

===Pronunciation===
*{{IPA|/gaɪl/}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun|s|-}}
#{{uncountable}} [[astuteness|Astuteness]] often marked by a certain sense of [[cunning]] or [[artful]] [[deception]].
#{{countable}} an instance of this; a [[trick]]
#:*'''1999''': Although I'm closing in on 40, I'm still more than willing to pit my wits against the '''guiles''' of the mermaid's song. — John Kretschmer, ''Flirting with Mermaids'' (Sheridan House 2003, p. 9)

